    <li id="fn:fn1" role="doc-endnote">

      <p>The author had just landed in La Guardia Airport after the flight captain died. All the passengers stood up to applaud the co-pilot. We have it in good authority that the event in question led Yoko Ono to write her “Letter to John”:</p>

      <blockquote class="poetry">
        <ul>
          <li>On a windy day let’s go flying</li>
          <li>There may be no trees to rest on</li>
          <li>There may be no clouds to ride</li>
          <li>But we’ll have our wings and the wind will be with us</li>
          <li>That’s enough for me, that’s enough for me.</li>
        </ul>
      </blockquote>
